10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Framer is best suited for designers, startups, portfolio sites, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Galileo AI, meanwhile, shines for designers seeking inspiration, product teams, rapid ideation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, Framer describes itself as \"AI-powered website builder with professional design and CMS capabilities.\" Galileo AI, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI design tool that generates editable UI designs from text prompts.\" With 9 years between them, Framer brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Galileo AI offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Framer** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Galileo AI is a poor choice — far from it. Galileo AI excels in its own right, particularly for designers seeking inspiration and product teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value beautiful design-first website builder, go with Framer. If impressive ai-generated ui quality matters more to you, Galileo AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
